{"title_page": "Talent Plze\u0148", "text_new": "{{Third-party|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox handball club|\n|clubname=Talent Plze\u0148\n|image=\n|fullname=SSK Talent M.A.T. Plze\u0148\n|nickname=\n|founded=1953\n|ground=[[M\u011bstsk\u00e1 sportovn\u00ed hala Plze\u0148]]\n|capacity=1,350\n|league=[[Czech Handball Extraliga]]\n|season=2019-20\n|website=https://talentplzen.cz/}}\n\n'''SSK Talent M.A.T Plze\u0148''' or '''Talent Plze\u0148''' is a Czech [[handball]] club based in the [[Plze\u0148]], [[Czech Republic]]. Talent Plze\u0148 is one of the most successful handball club in the country, having won the [[Czech Handball Extraliga]] six times.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.talentplzen.cz/|title=Information|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe club was founded in 1953. Talent Plze\u0148 win the first title in 1973 in [[Czechoslovak Handball League]]. The club was doing well in the 1998 and 1999, when won [[Czech Handball Extraliga]].[[TJ Lokomotiva Plze\u0148]] and SSK Talent Plze\u0148 affiliated in 2010. The club has been doing well in recent season, because the club won [[Czech Handball Extraliga ]] 3 times and finished 2x second.\n\n== Accompliishments ==\n\n* '''[[Czech Handball Extraliga]]:'''\n** {{gold medal}}: 1998, 1999, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2019\n** {{silver medal}}: 2017, 2018\n** {{bronze medal}}: 2000,\n== Europan Records ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n! Season \n! Round \n! Club \n! Home \n! Away\n! Aggregate:\n|-\n|rowspan=1 bgcolor=white| [[1998-99 EHF Champions League|1998-99]]\n| align=center| 1/16\n|{{flagicon|MKD}} [[RK Pelister, Bitola|RK Pelister Bitola]]\n|align=center|30-22\n|align=center|27-30\n|align=center|57-52\n|-\n|rowspan=3 bgcolor=white| [[1998-99 EHF Champions League|1998-99]]\n| align=center| Group D\n|{{flagicon|SLO}} [[Celje Pivovarna Lasko]]\n|align=center|21-27\n|align=center|22-38\n| align=center  rowspan=3|\n4<small>rd</sma