] club based in the [[Plze\u0148]], [[Czech Republic]]. Talent Plze\u0148 is one of the most successful handball club in the country, having won the [[Czech Handball Extraliga]] six times.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.talentplzen.cz/|title=Information|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe club was founded in 1953. Talent Plze\u0148 win the first title in 1973 in [[Czechoslovak Handball League]]. The club was doing well in the 1998 and 1999, when won [[Czech Handball Extraliga]].[[TJ Lokomotiva Plze\u0148]] and SSK Talent Plze\u0148 affiliated in 2010. The club has been doing well in recent season, because the club won [[Czech Handball Extraliga ]] 3 times and finished 2x second.\n\n== Accompliishments ==\n\n* '''[[Czech Handball Extraliga]]:'''\n** {{gold medal}}: 1998, 1999, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2019\n** {{silver medal}}: 2017, 2018\n** {{bronze medal}}: 2000,\n== Europan Records ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n! Season \n! Round \n! Club \n! Home \n! Away\n! Aggregate:\n|-\n|rowspan=1 bgcolor=white| [[1998-99 EHF Champions League|1998-99]]\n| align=center| 1/16\n|{{flagicon|MKD}} [[RK Pelister, Bitola|RK Pelister Bitola]]\n|align=center|30-22\n|align=center|27-30\n|align=center|57-52\n|-\n|rowspan=3 bgcolor=white| [[1998-99 EHF Champions League|1998-99]]\n| align=center| Group D\n|{{flagicon|SLO}} [[Celje Pivovarna Lasko]]\n|align=center|21-27\n|align=center|22-38\n| align=center  rowspan=3|\n4<small>rd</small>\n|-\n| align=center| Group D\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[SDC San Antonio|Portland San Antonio]]\n|align=center|26-32\n|align=center|22-28\n|-\n| align=center| Group D \n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Redbergslids IK|Redbergslids G\u00f6teborg]]\n|align=center|18-25\n|align=center|20-29\n|-\n|rowspan=1 bgcolor=white| [[2014-15 EHF Cup|2014-15]]\n| align=center|R1\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[SSV Bozen Loacker]]\n|align=center|26-26\n|align=center|24-17\n|align=center|50-43\n|-\n|rowspan